# Subagent Maintenance

## Purpose

Use this checklist whenever you add, rename, remove, or materially change a subagent.

## Gate

- First confirm that no existing specialist fits the work.
- Missing specialist coverage is a stop condition, not permission for the orchestrator to keep the task.
- Default model for a new specialist is `GPT-5.4-mini` unless a stronger lane is explicitly justified.

## Required update surfaces

1. Add or update the role card in `.cursor/agents/`
2. Update `docs/AGENT_REGISTRY.mdc`
3. Update `.cursor/rules/subagent-routing.mdc`
4. Update `docs/AGENT_ORCHESTRATION.mdc` if authority or handoff behavior changes
5. Update `docs/MODEL_ROUTING.mdc` if the model lane changes
6. Update `AGENTS.mdc` if the repo-level operating contract changes
7. If the lane owns product briefs or PRD-adjacent prose, confirm **`docs/product/`** (or linked canonical doc) stays accurate
8. Record the change in `docs/DECISION_LOG.mdc` if it affects governance
9. Update `docs/HYGIENE.mdc` if the lane affects cleanup or removal policy
10. Update `README.md` only if the top-level operating stance changes
11. If you are recording formal workflow validation evidence, append to `docs/WORKFLOW_VALIDATION.mdc`

## Add-a-subagent checklist

- define the mission clearly
- define inputs
- define output contract
- define stop conditions
- assign the default `GPT-5.4-mini` lane unless there is an explicit reason not to
- document any non-default model choice in the role card and `docs/MODEL_ROUTING.mdc`
- ensure packet usage is still valid
- note whether the subagent changes the visual or documentation system
- update `docs/AGENT_REGISTRY.mdc` and evidence surfaces when the lane becomes part of the official set

## Remove-or-merge checklist

- remove stale references from docs and rules
- confirm no skills still point at the old role
- note the reason in `docs/DECISION_LOG.mdc`
